OL,3,GWales
OL,4,
OL,5,CThis Evening and Tonight:FSunny spells
OL,6,Fthis evening but a few isolated
OL,7,Fshowers are possible in the north,
OL,8,Fperhaps continuing overnight.
OL,9,FGenerally dry otherwise with clear
OL,10,Fspells. Turning chilly with a patchy
OL,11,Frural grass frost, though this
OL,12,Fsomewhat less widespread than last
OL,13,Fnight.
OL,14,
OL,15,CTuesday:FDry with spells of cloudy
OL,16,Fweather interspersed with periods of
OL,17,Fsunshine, these most prolonged during
OL,18,Fthe afternoon. Feeling warm in the
OL,19,Fsunshine, though increasingly breezy
OL,20,Fwith an easterly wind developing.
OL,23,QppppppppppppppppppppGSource: Met Office
OL,24,ANext Page  BWeather  CReg News  FReg TV
